subsection.p:
Bernoulli's equation includes static behavior as we can see immediately by setting  v_1 = v_2 = 0 in the equation. 

	p_1 + \rho g h_1 = p_2 + \rho g h_2.  \ \ \text{(Static)}

If the area of pipe at the entrance and exit points are same, the speed of flow will be same, canceling the kinetic energy terms. This results in the same equation.

	p_1 + \rho g h_1 = p_2 + \rho g h_2.  \ \ \text{(Same Pipe Size at Ends)}

This says that work by the pressure difference between two points in a fluid at rest of having same criss-sections, provides the difference in the potential energy.

	p_1 -p_1 =  \rho g \left( h_2 - h_1 \right).
